author: @Hurairahgiri
comment:
I had tribit XSound Go. Loved it but after 4 years of use, its given up. Here is my experience using it. 
From the start, the rubberised coating was hard to clean and started getting slightly sticky. 
After 2 years of use, the cover for aux and usb c ports broke off. Meaning i cant bring it near water, never used to tbh. 
After 3.5 years, the power button cracked and broke off. So there was a hole. This completely changed how it sounded because now there was a hole. 
And as of last week, i can hear crackling sound. 

So yeah this is my experience using it. All the time i have stored it in its pouch and taken good care. Not sure if i should buy another tribit product or choose edifier.
